            <div class="Facts">
                <h3>What is?</h3>
                <p>  
                    Klepon is a traditional Indonesian sweet snack originating from Java, made from glutinous rice flour dough 
                    filled with palm sugar and coated with grated coconut. These bite-sized green balls are boiled until they 
                    float, indicating they are cooked, then rolled in coconut flakes. Once bitten into, the palm sugar filling
                    oozes out, providing a delightful burst of sweetness that contrasts beautifully with the chewy texture of 
                    the rice cake. Klepon is a popular treat enjoyed as a snack or dessert, appreciated for its unique 
                    combination of flavors and textures, making it a beloved part of Indonesian culinary culture.
                </p>
            </div>
