                <ol>
                    <li>Mix the glutinous rice powder with lukewarm water and green food coloring until it forms a firm but flexible dough.</li>
                    <li>Pull off one full teaspoon of the dough and shape it into a ball approximately 2Â½ cm (1 inch) in diameter.</li>
                    <li>Press a finger into the center of the ball to make a hole, then add approximately Â½ tsp. of grated sugar. Seal the hole and roll the ball back into shape with the palms of your hands.</li>
                    <li>Repeat the process for all the dough, shaping them into balls and setting them aside.</li>
                    <li>Fill a pot halfway with water and bring it to a boil.</li>
                    <li>Drop the balls into the boiling water. Remove them with a spoon once they float to the water's surface, then roll them in grated coconut.</li>
